## Keyboard Navigation

### Skip link (first focusable element on page)
```html
<a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:fixed focus:top-4 focus:left-4">
  Skip to main content
</a>
<main id="main-content">...</main>
```

### Focus visibility (WCAG 2.2: 2px min, 3:1 contrast)
```css
/* Never do this */
*:focus { outline: none; }

/* CORRECT — visible focus for keyboard, hidden for mouse */
*:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid oklch(60% 0.2 250);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

### tabIndex rules
```tsx
<button>             // tabIndex=0 implicitly — do this
<div tabIndex={0}>   // only when making custom interactive element
<div tabIndex={-1}>  // programmatic focus only (modals, auto-focus)
<div tabIndex={1}>   // NEVER positive tabIndex — breaks natural order
```

### Roving tabIndex for composite widgets (listbox, toolbar, menu)
```tsx
function MenuBar({ items }) {
  const [activeIdx, setActiveIdx] = useState(0);
  return (
    <div role="menubar">
      {items.map((item, i) => (
        <button
          key={item.id}
          role="menuitem"
          tabIndex={i === activeIdx ? 0 : -1}  // only active item in tab order
          onKeyDown={(e) => {
            if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') setActiveIdx((i + 1) % items.length);
            if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft')  setActiveIdx((i - 1 + items.length) % items.length);
          }}
        >
          {item.label}
        </button>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Contrast + Motion

### Contrast ratios (WCAG 2.1/2.2 AA)
| Text | Ratio |
|------|-------|
| Normal text (<18pt / <14pt bold) | ≥ 4.5:1 |
| Large text (≥18pt / ≥14pt bold) | ≥ 3:1 |
| UI components, focus rings | ≥ 3:1 vs adjacent |

```bash
# Tools
npx accessible-colors                # CLI contrast checker
# Browser: Chrome DevTools > Accessibility > Contrast Ratio
# Design: Figma plugins — A11y Annotation Kit, Stark
```

### prefers-reduced-motion
```css
/* Default: full animation */
.card { transition: transform 300ms ease; }

/* Reduced: no transform, instant or opacity-only */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .card { transition: opacity 150ms ease; transform: none !important; }
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

```tsx
// React hook for conditional animation
function useReducedMotion() {
  return window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
}

const isReduced = useReducedMotion();
<motion.div
  animate={{ x: isReduced ? 0 : 100 }}
  transition={{ duration: isReduced ? 0 : 0.5 }}
/>
```

**Never** use color as the only way to convey information (errors, status, etc.).

## Focus Management in Modals

### Using Radix/shadcn Dialog (recommended)
Radix UI handles focus trap automatically via `@radix-ui/react-dialog`:
```tsx
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTitle } from '@/components/ui/dialog';
// Focus automatically trapped inside DialogContent
// Focus restored to trigger on close
```

### Manual focus trap (when building custom)
```tsx
function Dialog({ open, onClose, children }) {
  const dialogRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
  const prevFocusRef = useRef<Element | null>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (open) {
      prevFocusRef.current = document.activeElement;
      // Move focus into dialog
      const firstFocusable = dialogRef.current?.querySelector<HTMLElement>(
        'button, [href], input, select, textarea, [tabindex]:not([tabindex="-1"])'
      );
      firstFocusable?.focus();
    } else {
      // Restore focus to trigger element
      (prevFocusRef.current as HTMLElement)?.focus();
    }
  }, [open]);

  return open ? (
    <div ref={dialogRef} role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
      {children}
    </div>
  ) : null;
}
```

### inert attribute (modern approach)
```tsx
// Prevent background from receiving focus/clicks while dialog is open
<main inert={dialogOpen}>  {/* all focusable elements inside are disabled */}
  <RestOfApp />
</main>
<Dialog open={dialogOpen}>...</Dialog>
```

**Rules:**
- Always use `aria-modal="true"` on dialogs
- Never leave focus stuck inside a closed dialog
- Announce dialog title via `aria-labelledby`
